      "lesson title": "Clinical Decision Support Systems: Safe Usage Boundaries",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Clinical decision support systems (CDSS) can be powerful tools for helping healthcare professionals gather information, identify patterns, and flag potential risks. However, understanding where these systems are most useful, and where their limitations begin, is essential for safe clinical practice. This lesson introduces the concept of safe usage boundaries, exploring the types of decisions that benefit from AI support and those that require human clinical judgement above all else. You will learn to recognise situations where over-reliance on automated recommendations could pose a risk to patient safety, and how to maintain your professional accountability throughout. By the end of this lesson, you will feel more confident in using clinical decision support tools appropriately, as a helpful aid rather than a replacement for your own expertise.",
